{"Title":"Mixing Server Side Javascript and HTML","Contents":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\">\u003C/blockquote>\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\" style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 119); \">About ObjectCloud\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\" style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 119); \">\u003Cbr>\u003C/a>\u003C/p>\u003Cblockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\">\u003Cp>\u003Cb>Note\u003C/b>: &nbsp;\u003Ci>Mixing HTML with server-side Javascript is a new and experimental feature. &nbsp;This page was written quickly.\u003C/i>\u003C/p>\u003C/blockquote>\u003Cp>Sometimes it is&nbsp;necessary&nbsp;to mix server-side Javascript and HTML. &nbsp;For example, when serving to a mobile platform, performing rendering logic in client-side Javascript could impede performance. &nbsp;Likewise, there might be some special HTML or other logic needed for legacy situations.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>For more information about the built-in functions with server-side Javascript, see \u003Ca href=\"/Docs/server side JS.page\" title=\"\" target=\"\">Secure Storage with Server-Side Javascript\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Any text file with a .ssjs extension can contain Javascript within &lt;? and ?&gt; tags. &nbsp;The result of executing the Javascript determines how all text until the next &lt;? ?&gt; tag is rendered:\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003C/p>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cb>string, number, or function\u003C/b>: &nbsp;If the Javascript results in a string, number, or function, the value is inserted into the HTML.\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cb>null or undefined\u003C/b>: &nbsp;If null or undefined is returned, then nothing is mixed into the HTML.\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cb>boolean\u003C/b>: &nbsp;If a boolean is returned, then all of the HTML until the next &lt;? ?&gt; is displayed only if true is returned. &nbsp;If false is returned, the HTML is omitted.\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cb>object\u003C/b>: &nbsp;If a Javascript object is returned, it allows for&nbsp;substitution&nbsp;in all of the HTML until the next &lt;? ?&gt; tag. &nbsp;For each property, values with the property name enclosed in % are replaced. &nbsp;For example, an object like { a: 'aaaa', b: 'bbb'} would replace \"&lt;p&gt; %a% %b% &lt;/p&gt;\" with \"&lt;p&gt; aaaa bbb &lt;/p&gt;\"\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cb>array\u003C/b>: &nbsp;If an array is returned, ObjectCloud performs the above behavior for each element. &nbsp;This allows for a single bit of HTML to be repeated if multiple objects are returned.\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003Cp>Note: &nbsp;To return JSON, use JSON.stringify().\u003C/p>The following example creates the following HTML:\u003Cp>\u003C/p>\u003Cblockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\">\u003Cpre>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN\"\n\"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd\"&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n   &lt;head&gt;\n      &lt;? Scripts(/API/Prototype.js) ?&gt;\n      &lt;title&gt;Test of SSJS system&lt;/title&gt;\n      &lt;link href=\"/Pages/objectcloud.css\" type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" /&gt;\n      &lt;link href=\"/API/proto.menu.css\" type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" /&gt;\n   &lt;/head&gt;\n   &lt;body&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;Loading server-side JS:\n      &lt;?\n         try\n         {\n            var result = use('/API/AJAX_serverside.js');\n            \"loaded \" + result;\n         }\n         catch (exception)\n         {\n           exception;\n         }\n      ?&gt;\n   &lt;/p&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;Loading another object:\n      &lt;?\n         try\n         {\n            var result = open('/API');\n            \"loaded \" + result;\n         }\n         catch (exception)\n         {\n           exception;\n         }\n      ?&gt;\n   &lt;/p&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;Number: &lt;? var e = 1+1; e; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;String: &lt;? \"foo\"; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Function: &lt;? function(){}; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Exception: &lt;? throw \"exp\"; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Syntax error: &lt;? retur ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Null: &lt;? null; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Array (note the no-op): &lt;? [1, 'aaa', 86]; ?&gt;&lt;/br&gt; &lt;? ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;True (note the no-op): &lt;? true; ?&gt;true&lt;? ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;False (note the no-op): &lt;? false; ?&gt;false&lt;? ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;Replacements: &lt;? var toReturn = {a: 'aaaaaa', b: 'bbbbbbb'}; toReturn; ?&gt;\n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: %a% &lt;li&gt;b: %b%&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;? ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;Multiple Replacements: \n      &lt;?\n         [{a: 'aaaaaa', b: 'bbbbbbb'},{a: 'aaa', b: 'bbb'},{a: 1, b: 2}];\n      ?&gt;\n\n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: %a% &lt;li&gt;b: %b%&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;? ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n   &lt;p&gt;JSON: &lt;? JSON.stringify({a: 'a', b: 'b'}); ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n   &lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\u003Cbr>\u003C/pre>\u003C/blockquote>\u003Cp>Resulting HTML:\u003C/p>\u003Cblockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\">\u003Cpre>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN\"\n\"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd\"&gt; \n&lt;html&gt; \n   &lt;head&gt; \n      &lt;script src=\"/API/Prototype.js?BrowserCache=LyY9krEuP0mduQEXeXq9FA%3D%3D&amp;EncodeFor=JavaScript\" &gt;&lt;/script&gt; \n      &lt;title&gt;Test of SSJS system&lt;/title&gt; \n      &lt;link href=\"/Pages/objectcloud.css\" type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" /&gt; \n      &lt;link href=\"/API/proto.menu.css\" type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" /&gt; \n   &lt;/head&gt; \n   &lt;body&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;Loading server-side JS:\n      loaded undefined\n   &lt;/p&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;Loading another object:\n      loaded [object Object]\n   &lt;/p&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;Number: 2&lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;String: foo&lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;Function: \nfunction () {\n}\n&lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;Exception: exp &lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;Syntax error: ReferenceError: \"retur\" is not defined. &lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;Null: &lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;Array (note the no-op): 1&lt;/br&gt; aaa&lt;/br&gt; 86&lt;/br&gt; &lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;True (note the no-op): true&lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;p&gt;False (note the no-op): &lt;/p&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;Replacements: \n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: aaaaaa &lt;li&gt;b: bbbbbbb&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;Multiple Replacements: \n      \n \n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: aaaaaa &lt;li&gt;b: bbbbbbb&lt;/ul&gt; \n \n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: aaa &lt;li&gt;b: bbb&lt;/ul&gt; \n \n      &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;a: 1 &lt;li&gt;b: 2&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n \n   &lt;p&gt;JSON: {\"a\":\"a\",\"b\":\"b\"}&lt;/p&gt; \n   &lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt;\u003Cbr>\u003C/pre>\u003C/blockquote>\u003Ch1>Scope\u003C/h1>\u003Cp>Each &lt;? ?&gt; is its own scope. &nbsp;Unlike in-browser Javascript, variables declared in one &lt;? ?&gt; bracket are not available in later brackets. &nbsp;To make data available, an object called \"scope\" is shared among all brackets.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Example:\u003C/p>\u003Cblockquote class=\"webkit-indent-blockquote\" style=\"margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;\">\u003Cpre>&lt;? scope.a = 'fsfds' ?&gt;\u003C/pre>\u003Cpre>&lt;? scope.a += 'append' ?&gt;\u003C/pre>\u003C/blockquote>"}